post_text:
We're doing Tractor Raffle ticket sales the next 2 weekends at the Antique Tractor Show at the Mattoon Mall. We could use a few more adult volunteers to sit with FFA members and help sell tickets. We're selling from 4 - close on Thurs and Fri. and f ru om 12 noon to close on Sat. If we can get some more volunteers, we'd like to sell from 12 - 4 on Sunday. Consider helping for a 2 or 4 hour shift. Also, if you have an FFA member that can help have them contact me at 217 - 259 - 5628. FFA members should wear their official FFA dress.

Thanks
Tom Strohl

post_text:
Come Help us celebrate FFA Week with the local Neoga FFA Chapter.!

On Thursday, February 21:

5:00 p.m. FFA food and drinks in the Ag Shop - Alumni members, their guests, or prospective Alumni members are welcome to attend. To ensure there is enough food, RSVP to me a head count by noon Wednesday, February 20, 2019. Send your RSVP to me by either email ( ctstrohl@frontier.com or text 217-259-5628 ).

After dining with the FFA Chapter , we have been CHALLENGED to form a team or teams and compete in their

AG OLYMPICS

in the Ag Shop beginning at 6:00 PM .

Let's show our support for the local chapter by 'fielding' a team. (4 - 8 persons / team). If you are willing to show your support by being on a team, let me know by Thursday noon.

Finally, as part of the events for the week, we will be holding our next

Alumni Meeting

this Thursday, February 21, 2019 at 7:00 PM in the NHS AG room.

Plan on attending, and participating as we begin our 2019 Support for our next generation of leaders.

Please SHARE with your friends!

Facts about the NEOGA FFA ALUMNI

1. We are here to support the FFA students and their advisor. This may mean volunteering, donating, or just mentoring!

2. You do NOT have to be a previous FFA member to join.

3. Joining is easy! Just message us for more details!
